-- Malawi Government Forms Committee to Oversee Corruption Fight, MBC Says
-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 2010-12-17T08:20:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/malawi-governemtn-forms-committee-to-oversee-corruption-fight-mbc-says.html
Malawi set up a National Integrity
Committee to oversee the country’s anti-corruption program,
state-run Malawi Broadcasting Corp. reported, citing President
 Bingu wa Mutharika’s  office.  The committee will look at the government’s performance in
tackling corruption and offer advice to the Anti-Corruption
Bureau, the Blantyre-based broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre via Johannesburg at
   fjomo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 